.TH ZTRUNC 3 libzahl
.SH NAME
ztrunc - Truncate a big integer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <zahl.h>

void ztrunc(z_t \fIa\fP, z_t \fIb\fP, size_t \fIbits\fP);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ztrunc
makes a truncated copy of
.I b
and stores it in
.I a .
Only the first
.I bits
from
.I b
and
.IR b 's
sign is copied to
.I a .
.P
It is safe to call
.B zsplit
with non-unique parameters.
.SH RATIONALE
This was useful for improving the performance of
.BR zsplit (3).
